-- MORE: Turkey Court Hearing Coup Plot Trial Cites Terror Threat
-- B y   S e l c a n   H a c a o g l u
-- 2013-08-05T08:29:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-05/more-turkey-court-hearing-coup-plot-trial-cites-terror-threat.html
Intelligence reports of plans to
attack judges prompt heavy security at court that is to deliver
verdict today in Erdogan coup plot case, state-run Anatolia news
agency says.
* Court says militant Marxist group, the Revolutionary Peoples’
Liberation Party-Front, or DHKP-C, has planned attacks: Anatolia
* Paramilitary police blocked roads leading to courthouse in
Silivri near Istanbul, Tolga Emek, local official of main
opposition Republican People’s Party, says by telephone today
* NOTE: Suspected DHKP-C militants captured along with
explosives, other weapons, on Turkey-bound boat by Greek Coast
Guard earlier this month
* NOTE: 275 secularists,  including top generals, journalists,
academics and lawmakers, accused of plotting to overthrow Prime
Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan’s Islamist-rooted govt  To contact the reporter on this story:
